r beyond the range of a contemporary academic anthology, constituting instead a dynamic think tank on the concept of Jewish peoplehood by bringing together intellectuals from France, Israel, the UK, and the United States. The collection offers both intellectual and practical frameworks for grappling with the policy outcomes of different understandings of the peoplehood concept, and contributors to this volume include noted figures from diverse walks of life: academic disciplines in the social sciences and humanities, a rabbi, a literary figure, and communal leaders.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aIsrael and the diasporavCongresses. 0aJewszIsraelxIdentityvCongresses. 0aJewszIsraelxPolitics and governmentvCongresses. 0aJewszUnited StatesxIdentityvCongresses. 0aJewszUnited StatesxPolitics and governmentvCongresses. 0aJudaismy21st centuryvCongresses. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Jewish Studies.2bisacsh1 aAriel, Yonatan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBouganim, Ami, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisen, Arnold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeller, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGovrin, Michal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalbertal, Moshe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffmann, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKopelowitz, Ezra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKopelowitz, Ezra, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPrell, Riv-Ellen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRevivi, Menachem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators